00:00:04.480 --> 00:00:05.480
1.

00:00:05.480 --> 00:00:09.089
The “Hercules beetle” lives in the rainforests
of Central and South America and is known

00:00:09.089 --> 00:00:14.909
for being able to lift more than 850 times
its own weight, or about 8 kilograms (17.6

00:00:14.909 --> 00:00:15.909
lbs).

00:00:15.909 --> 00:00:19.260
Pound for pound, this makes it one of the
strongest animals on the planet.

00:00:19.260 --> 00:00:24.810
For reference, if a 90 kg (200 lb) male human
could do the same, he would be able to lift

00:00:24.810 --> 00:00:29.789
76,500 kg or 170,000 lbs.

00:00:29.789 --> 00:00:32.130
(QF: 721)
2.

00:00:32.130 --> 00:00:36.250
Cats are the only known animal, including
humans, that prefer to be given things freely,

00:00:36.250 --> 00:00:38.680
rather than needing to do some task to get
them.

00:00:38.680 --> 00:00:39.680
Don’t believe us?

00:00:39.680 --> 00:00:43.030
Google Contrafreeloading if you’re interested
